column1: # FOFEM Species File - Updated DCL Feb. 16 2017
# This file is used in conjunction with the FOFEM tree mortality option
# Mort = Pre-Fire mortality equation number
# Brk  = Bark Equation
# Reg  = Region
#          Interior West   1
#          Pacific West    2
#          North East      3
#          South East      4
# Crn  = Crown Coefficient code used to calculate stand canopy cover
# PF   = Post-Fire mortality equation code. See Note-1 below.
# P    = A "P" in this column will cause the species to be displayed
#        in only the list of post-fire mortality equations
# Note-1: Ponderosa pine and Jeffrey pine have two post-fire mortality
#         equations. Equation code "PP" corresponds to the mortality
#         equation that uses crown volume scorched and equation code
#        "PK" corresponds to the mortality equation that uses
#         crown volume killed (bud kill). Species codes for ponderosa
#        pine and Jeffrey pine that end in "K" are assigned to the
#         equations that use crown volume killed (bud kill) in the
#         mortality equation. E.g. PIPOK and PIJEK use crown kill
# 	  to estimate mortality.

column3: Pinus ponderosa -- Ponderosa Pine Black Hills
